      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must have documented V&V test suite with version-controlled release notes and issue tracking.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2024 R1 is used under a validated software environment with documented QA procedures, regression test suite, and configuration management. Software version is locked and traceable to the simulation archive."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation via benchmark problems with known analytical solutions at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed against Poiseuille flow and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Observed order of accuracy is consistent with theoretical second-order convergence. Results archived in the simulation verification report SVR-2024-07."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for primary QoI (hemolysis index) with GCI < 5% on the fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on the nominal pump geometry. GCI for the normalized hemolysis index is 3.2% on the fine mesh (12.4M cells), confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented and traceable, with boundary conditions matching CFD inputs within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments conducted at five flow-speed operating points (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) using bovine blood at 37°C. Inlet pressure and flow rate measured with calibrated instrumentation. Experimental uncertainty documented in test report TR-2025-03."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized hemolysis index RH must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RH values fall within ±12% of experimental measurements across all five operating points. The maximum deviation of 11.7% at 6 L/min / 3500 RPM is within the combined uncertainty band. Output comparison is documented in validation report VR-2025-11."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly linked to the clinical risk metric (hemolysis) and the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "The normalized hemolysis index RH is the primary QoI and directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) are correlated with hemolysis mechanisms and support mechanistic interpretation of RH predictions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid properties, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry with bovine blood (viscosity and density matched to human blood within 4%). Operating conditions span the full CPB clinical envelope. Validation is judged relevant to the COU with no material extrapolation beyond the validated domain."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; iterative convergence monitored via residuals only.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal quantification of iterative solver error is not required. Residuals are monitored to below 1e-5 for all equations. No formal iterative error budget is compiled."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst training records reviewed informally.",
      "rationale": "Simulation analysts hold advanced degrees in computational fluid dynamics and have completed internal CFD competency review. Formal use-error assessment is not required at MRL 2 for this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection documented in modeling report.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model with low-Reynolds corrections is selected based on literature precedent for rotating blood pump flows. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be traceable to measurement data or published literature values with stated uncertainty. Input sensitivity must be documented for the primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, rotational speed) are derived from experimental measurements in dataset morrison-cpb-piv-benchmark-2025. Blood rheology parameters are taken from published Carreau-Yasuda fits. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis confirms RH is most sensitive to rotational speed (±2.3% per 1% speed change) and least sensitive to inlet velocity profile shape (±0.4%). The benchmark PIV dataset used for boundary condition specification carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-21, which predates the model revision of 2025-11-14 by approximately three weeks. The model revision addressed a minor correction to the impeller trailing-edge geometry discretization; the assessment team judged this change not material to the inlet and outlet boundary condition datasets, and no formal re-validation of the input dataset against the revised geometry was performed. This judgment is recorded in engineering change notice ECN-2025-047 but has not been independently verified through updated sensitivity analysis against the revised model build."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; sample characterization documented in test report.",
      "rationale": "Bovine blood samples used in hemolysis experiments were obtained from a single vendor lot and characterized for hematocrit (40 ± 2%) and plasma free hemoglobin prior to testing. Formal test-sample uncertainty propagation is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD boundary conditions must be demonstrably equivalent to experimental conditions within stated uncertainty, with documented mapping from measured quantities to model inputs.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles measured by PIV at the pump inlet plane are mapped directly to CFD inlet boundary conditions via area-weighted averaging. Flow rate agreement between PIV-integrated flux and Coriolis meter measurement is within 1.8% across all operating points. Rotational speed is matched to within 0.5 RPM. Equivalency is documented in boundary condition mapping report BCM-2025-09."
    }
  ],
